### TASK
Convert the target roleplay turn into strict third-person, past-tense narrative prose while enforcing verbatim structural retention.

### CHARACTER DESIGNATIONS
{# Use a namespace object to persist assignments outside of the loop block #}
{%- set ns = namespace(target_char=None) -%}
{%- set secondary_chars = [] -%}

{%- for identity in session.meta.identities -%}
    {%- if identity.entity_id == target_turn.actor_id -%}
        {%- set ns.target_char = identity -%}
    {%- else -%}
        {%- set _ = secondary_chars.append(identity) -%}
    {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}

- Target Actor Name: "{{ ns.target_char.name if ns.target_char else 'The Character' }}"
  Gender/Pronouns: {{ ns.target_char.gender if ns.target_char else 'unknown' }} ({% if ns.target_char %}{{ ns.target_char.pronouns.subjective }}/{{ ns.target_char.pronouns.objective }}/{{ ns.target_char.pronouns.possessive }}{% else %}they/them/their{% endif %})

- Secondary Character(s):
{%- for sec in secondary_chars %}
  * Name: "{{ sec.name }}" | Gender/Pronouns: {{ sec.gender }} ({{ sec.pronouns.subjective }}/{{ sec.pronouns.objective }}/{{ sec.pronouns.possessive }})
{%- else %}
  * None registered.
{%- endfor %}

### CHRONOLOGICAL HISTORY CONTEXT
Use this context solely for establishing continuity, tracking gender consistency, and locking down pronoun mappings. Do NOT modify or repeat this data.
{% for past_item in history_context if past_item.kind == 'turn' -%}
    {# Resolve the historical actor's name dynamically from the registry #}
    {%- set past_char_name = "Unknown" -%}
    {%- for identity in session.meta.identities -%}
        {%- if identity.entity_id == past_item.actor_id -%}{%- set past_char_name = identity.name -%}{%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
* {{ past_char_name }}: {{ past_item.prose }}
{%- endfor %}

### REWRITE RULES
1. TENSE & PERSPECTIVE CHANGE: Shift the targeted turn's active inline text exclusively to third-person past-tense. Use the provided pronoun set ({% if ns.target_char %}{{ ns.target_char.pronouns.subjective }}/{{ ns.target_char.pronouns.objective }}{% else %}they/them{% endif %}) to maintain absolute grammatical stability.
2. PROPER NOUN INJECTION: You must explicitly drop the proper names of BOTH characters at least once in the rewritten text to ground perspective instead of relying solely on generic pronouns.
3. SPOKEN TEXT DIRECTIVE: Keep spoken sentences verbatim with all typos/errors intact. Append a simple dialogic tag using the proper noun or pronoun (e.g., "he said", "she noted", "{{ ns.target_char.name if ns.target_char else 'he' }} asked").
4. THOUGHT TEXT DIRECTIVE: Keep thought fragments verbatim with all typos/errors intact, wrapped exclusively in *asterisks*.

